.TH LF 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lf \- list files in a directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lf
.RI [ directory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lf
lists the names of all entries in
.IR directory ,
one per line, sorted alphabetically.
If no directory is given, the current directory is listed.
Hidden files (those beginning with
.BR . )
are included.
This is a minimal JLC equivalent of
.BR ls (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open directory.
.TP
.B 3
Memory allocation failure.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List the current directory:
.B lf
.TP
List a specific directory:
.EX
lf /etc
.EE
.TP
Pipe to jgrep to filter:
.EX
lf /usr/bin | jgrep py
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ls (1),
.BR cwd (1),
.BR jgrep (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
